Two M60's.... that's impressive ! I knew one grunt who did just that.. one in parts and one if firing order.. Called him &quot;Big John&quot; and he was at that. Fire a 60 on the ground impressive but to hand hold more like a buck'n horse.<br><br>
Saw some'n really impressive once.. a Marine with a 50cal...with a star-light mounted on it... Now there is a SERIOUS Marine !<br><br>
Jokes aside, Marines have been the butt of a lot of Jokes but for one when the sh*t started to fly they come in damn handy.... just have to keep an eye on them when they layout a string of claymores........<br><br>
Numbness vs deinal skills... Don't know which or either, all I know is the emotions of the loss of those people is as fresh and powerful in my mind today as it was then. <br><br>
Reg Capt Dimmitt.. Funny how that works tain't it.. just like a 1st LT we had in 1/327 called him 'Buck' there are those who serve.. then there are those who serve with distinction... Not that I liked every order what came down, but as someone only said.. I've seen the boss job.. AND I DON'T WANT IT !'<br><br>
Tank's for offer of help... it's like a know the answers but just can't find the questions to put them to.... 10-4 ? <br><br>

